message.entry: Function handle MAP must return an n-by-3 colormap array.
Region number {0,number,integer} has the same color as the ZEROCOLOR.
Invalid colormap: MAP must be an n-by-3 double matrix with real values between 0 and 1 inclusive.
Invalid RGB triplet entry for ZEROCOLOR: ZEROCOLOR must be a 1-by-3 double vector with real values between 0 and 1 inclusive.
Valid entries for ORDER are ''shuffle'',''noshuffle'' or ''contrasting-neighbors''.
Ambiguous string or character vector for ORDER: {0}.
In code generation, at least two input arguments are required for LABEL2RGB.
In code generation, LABEL2RGB does not support colormap functions for MAP.
Entry for ZEROCOLOR is not part of the ColorSpec.
In code generation, ORDER can only be ''noshuffle''.
Invalid colormap: MAP must have at least as many colors as the number of labels in label matrix L.
